Here’s a **clear, production‑ready `useThrottle` hook** with **real React examples**, exactly how it’s expected in interviews and real projects.

***

# ✅ 1️⃣ Basic `useThrottle` Hook (Throttle a VALUE)

✅ Most common pattern  
✅ Useful for **scroll, resize, live metrics**

***

### ✅ `useThrottle` Hook Implementation

```jsx
import { useState, useEffect, useRef } from "react";

function useThrottle(value, delay) {
  const [throttledValue, setThrottledValue] = useState(value);
  const lastExecuted = useRef(Date.now());

  useEffect(() => {
    const now = Date.now();

    if (now - lastExecuted.current >= delay) {
      setThrottledValue(value);
      lastExecuted.current = now;
    }
  }, [value, delay]);

  return throttledValue;
}
```

***

### ✅ Usage Example (Scroll Position)

```jsx
function ScrollTracker() {
  const [scrollY, setScrollY] = useState(0);
  const throttledScrollY = useThrottle(scrollY, 1000);

  useEffect(() => {
    const onScroll = () => setScrollY(window.scrollY);
    window.addEventListener("scroll", onScroll);

    return () => window.removeEventListener("scroll", onScroll);
  }, []);

  useEffect(() => {
    console.log("Throttled scroll:", throttledScrollY);
  }, [throttledScrollY]);

  return <div style={{ height: "200vh" }}>Scroll down</div>;
}
```

✅ Updates **once per second**, even if scroll fires continuously

***

# ✅ 2️⃣ `useThrottledCallback` (Throttle a FUNCTION)

✅ Best for **event handlers**
✅ Closest to lodash `throttle`

***

### ✅ Hook Implementation

```jsx
import { useRef } from "react";

function useThrottledCallback(callback, delay) {
  const lastCall = useRef(0);

  return (...args) => {
    const now = Date.now();

    if (now - lastCall.current >= delay) {
      lastCall.current = now;
      callback(...args);
    }
  };
}
```

***

### ✅ Usage Example (Button Click Spam Prevention)

```jsx
function SubmitButton() {
  const handleClick = () => {
    console.log("Submitted at", new Date().toLocaleTimeString());
  };

  const throttledClick = useThrottledCallback(handleClick, 2000);

  return <button onClick={throttledClick}>Submit</button>;
}
```

✅ User can click many times  
✅ Function runs **only once every 2 seconds**

***

# ✅ 3️⃣ `useThrottle` Using `setTimeout` (Alternative)

✅ Guarantees delayed execution  
✅ More predictable behavior

***

### ✅ Hook Implementation

```jsx
import { useRef, useState, useEffect } from "react";

function useThrottle(value, delay) {
  const [throttledValue, setThrottledValue] = useState(value);
  const timerRef = useRef(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (!timerRef.current) {
      timerRef.current = setTimeout(() => {
        setThrottledValue(value);
        timerRef.current = null;
      }, delay);
    }

    return () => clearTimeout(timerRef.current);
  }, [value, delay]);

  return throttledValue;
}
```

